        "explanation": "In the word 'اَنْعَمْتَ', at the 2nd letter (position 2 of 5), we find Noon Sakin. The next letter 'ع' (within the same word) comes from the throat letters (حروف حلقي: ء ه ع ح غ خ). When this happens, we apply Izhar Halqi (إظهار حلقي), which means you must clearly pronounce the Noon without merging or nasalization. ",
